parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to a loss of braking power, increased stopping distance, and potentially, an accident.
symptoms: The brakes may lock up
the brake pedal may travel to the floor
there may be a burning smell
and the ABS light may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the rotors to overheat, leading to warping, cracking, or complete failure, which can result in a loss of braking power and potentially, an accident.
symptoms: The rotors may be warped
cracked
or damaged
and the brakes may vibrate or make noise when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the ABS and brake lights to illuminate, indicating a problem with the braking system, which can lead to a loss of braking power and potentially, an accident.
symptoms: The ABS and brake lights may illuminate
and the brakes may vibrate or make noise when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brakes smell hot
the brakes do not release properly
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control of the vehicle, making it difficult to steer, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering leaks at the weld of the rear housing
the power steering gear box fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause unexpected acceleration or deceleration, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The cruise control is repaired multiple times but never stays fixed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the liquid screen crystal display can cause the driver to lose access to critical information, such as speed, gear, and mileage, which can lead to reduced vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The display screen is blank or dark
the display screen is not showing any information
the display screen is not showing speed
gear
or mileage
the display screen is not functioning properly.
